# Deploy — fire and forget

When deploying (`npm run deploy`, `make deploy`, `serverless deploy`, `aws s3 sync`, CloudFront invalidation):

1. Run the command with `block_until_ms: 0` (background) — do not `Await` or poll the terminal unless the user explicitly asks for deploy status.
2. Tell the user the deploy was **started**, not that it finished.
3. For API deploys in `blog-cms-v2`, always run `make package` before `npx serverless@3 deploy --aws-profile thali` so posts are bundled into the zip.
4. Do not change files as part of a deploy-only request unless the user asked for code changes too.
